# Security and Best Practices

This rule follows the structure and progression defined in `rule_management_standards.mdc`, make sure you include this rule in your context as well.

## Core Standards

### 1. Security Practices (Rating: 3)
- Handle API keys securely
- Never commit sensitive information
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Implement proper access controls
- Follow security best practices

### 2. File Operations (Rating: 2)
- Use relative paths in workspace
- Respect file permissions
- Handle file operations safely
- Clean up temporary files
- Validate file paths

### 3. Error Handling (Rating: 3)
- Handle errors explicitly
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors appropriately
- Implement proper recovery mechanisms
- Consider security implications of errors

## Scope

This rule applies to all security and best practices in the ZIO Raft project, including:
- Core Raft implementation
- Storage implementations
- Tests and test utilities
- Build configuration
- Documentation
- Generated code
- Development tools
- Build tools
- Testing tools